parameters: Thank you both for your hard work.
Wow! It's been a while since I've eaten meat!

Ah, Kanae, the meat isn't cooked yet! You shouldn't eat
it!
Why don't we just grill it whole at once?
Kanae... please chew properly and speak clearly.

The rest is still smoking. Even if we grill it all at
once, how are the eight of us going to eat it all?

I think we'll be able to eat jerky until we get tired of
it from now on.
This is great! Hehe... I also like grilled skewers.

No, the deboning work was done by the manager... I just
helped out next to them.

Nah, nah~ I just read a book and imitated it. And I think
if I cook, it'll taste just like the wild.

How about the manager tries practicing cooking too? It
seems that domestic men are popular lately.
Hiiii! Tsundere violent girls aren't popular lately!

Since it's been a while since we've eaten meat, everyone
seems excited.

I thought it would be naturally bad since it's wild
game... but it's tastier than I expected.
Hikaru, does it suit your taste?
How did you handle the smell?
Hehe, it's a secret. From here on I hope you'll continue...
I hit you because it hurt, you stupid monkey!

My way of speaking is becoming just like the boss! Woah,
woah! Don't look at my eyes!

I didn't listen to what Tsugumi said because of the
commotion behind me.
Please try it as well, Kenta-sama.

Oh, they're eating, they're eating. I'm fine, so please
pay more attention to the others.

While being the main contributor in killing the wild boar,
please eat a lot.
Killing...? I don't think we should do that...
They seem to be having fun in their own way.

I approached Akane while holding a skewer with
delicious-looking grilled onions and wild boar meat
sandwiched together, along with a piece of lettuce.
Don't say it as if you've tried before.
Huh? Ah, I didn't mean it in that way...
Enjoy it! It's meat from an old man!

I hurriedly avoided Akane, who was swinging around the
finished skewer and ran away.
Hey, you seem to be becoming more and more like Saruyama.
Excuse me! Take this Grim Burst!
Oh, it looks like they're coming at us.

Y-You know, when I think about it carefully, it seems like
Hikaru has to take the shot.
Hit it as hard as you can!
No, who gave you permission to do as you please.
Don't get all touchy-feely so quickly!

The atmosphere during dinner is always lively and
cheerful, but today it's especially lively because it's
been a while since we had an all-you-can-eat barbecue.

There's no problem with drinking water... It doesn't feel like
we're stranded or anything.
The feeling of extending the camping a little longer.

I raised my head and looked up at the moon floating and
fluttering in the sky.

The soft curtain of light, scattered and obstructing the
darkness, blurred by the clouds, is a beautiful scenery
that can never be seen in the city.

Hikaru, who lacks a sense of crisis, took a bite of the
matured wild boar meat skewered in front of him and
fell into a moment of contemplation, wondering if even
such a romantic thought could come to mind.

I thought that for the first time in my life, my popular
phase had arrived.
